\begin{align*}
\cos \angle BHD &= \frac{BD^2 + DH^2 - BH^2}{2 \times BD \times DH} \\
&= \frac{DH^2 + DH^2 - BH^2}{2 \times DH \times DH} \\
&= \frac{2DH^2 - BH^2}{2DH^2}
\end{align*}
Using the given angles, we can find the lengths of DH, BH, and BD.
